items.title: Adding Payroll Featuresz
items.body:
To add payroll features to your QuickBooks account, follow these steps:
1. Navigate to Employees > Payroll Setup
2. Click on 'Set up payroll'
3. Choose your payroll plan (Basic, Enhanced, or Full Service)
4. Enter your business information
5. Add employee details
6. Set up payroll taxes
7. Complete payroll setup by following the on-screen instructions

items.title: Tax Form Filing Deadlines
items.body:
Here are the important tax filing deadlines:
- W-2 Forms: Must be provided to employees by January 31
- Quarterly Payroll Taxes (Form 941): Due at the end of the month following each quarter
- Annual Federal Unemployment (FUTA) Tax Return (Form 940): Due January 31
- 1099 Forms: Must be provided to contractors by January 31 and filed with the IRS by February 28

items.title: Setting Up International Payments
items.body:
To set up international payments in QuickBooks:
1. Go to Banking > Bank Feeds > Set Up Bank Feed
2. Select your bank or 'Connect to a different bank'
3. For international payments, select the currency
4. Enter your bank account details
5. Set up the payment method
6. Test the connection with a small transaction
7. Start using international payments
